( author: Sandro)
( file: manual_unload.ngc )
( purpose: Manually release/unload tool using the M6 T0 handshake )
( version: 1.0 )
( date: 2026-01-07 )

( Behavior:
    - Moves to safe Z (G53 Z0), stops spindle
    - Moves to the defined tool-change position using #5181/#5182/#5183
    - Calls M6 T0 (GUI/HAL shows the tool-change dialog; pneumatic clamp unlocks)
    - Waits for operator confirmation (via M6 handshake), then exits without probing
    - Cancels tool-length comp and clears logical tool state
)

o<manual_tool_release> sub

    (---- configuration / conventions ----)
    ( Uses the same parameter conventions as tool_touch_off.ngc )
    #<traverse_fr> = #3006         ( traverse feed from probe screen / your .var file )

    ( Change position coordinates are read from the machine registers )
    ( #5181 -> X, #5182 -> Y, #5183 -> Z-above-change position )
    #<chg_x> = #5181
    #<chg_y> = #5182
    #<chg_z> = #5183

    (---- safety prelude ----)
    G92.1                      ( cancel any G92 offset )
    M50 P0                     ( lock feed override during safety moves )
    G40                        ( cancel diameter comp just in case )
    G49                        ( cancel length comp )

    (---- go safe Z and stop spindle ----)
    G90
    G53 G1 F#<traverse_fr> Z0  ( safe Z first )
    M5                         ( stop spindle; if you use a different M, set via remap or edit here )
    M9                         ( coolant OFF if applicable )

    (---- move to tool-change position ----)
    G53 G1 F#<traverse_fr> X#<chg_x> Y#<chg_y>
    G53 G1 F#<traverse_fr> Z#<chg_z>

    ( Optional explicit hint; GUI will still show its own popup at M6 )
    (MSG, Unload tool (T0) and press Cycle Start)

    (---- request "no tool" using standard tool-change handshake ----)
    ( This triggers the pneumatic clamp unlock and waits for operator confirmation )
    M6 T0

    (---- cleanup / logical state ----)
    G49                        ( ensure no length comp active )
    M61 Q0                     ( set logical “no tool in spindle” )
    ; #3991 = 0               ( if your ATC/GUI uses this flag, uncomment to keep states consistent )

    M50 P1                     ( restore feed override behavior )

o<manual_tool_release> endsub

M2 ( end program )
